useradd deepak 
passwd deepak
enter password
vim /etc/sudoers
the file will open
press i to go to insert mode
search for ALL=(ALL ALL) 
under this line write : Deepak ALL=(ALL)  /user/sbin/useradd
to save and exit press esc+ colon+w+q+!+enter
login as deepak
then we have to login as deepak : sudo su - Deepak
sudo useradd jk
cat/etc/passwd | grep -i jk
